beer.beer_description:
For a few hundred years, Lichtenhainer has been brewed continuously. This brew is sour and smokey, thanks to its lightly smoked malt. It is known for its complex flavour and low bitterness. Surprisingly, our most popular Oktoberfest release.
⁠
Coat Of Arms: Jena⁠
⁠
MALTS: Beechwood Smoked, Pilsner, Vienna, Wheat⁠

HOPS: Hallertau Tradition⁠

items.badge_description: Your quest to quench your thirst leaves no stone unturned! That's at least 50 distinct venues!
